# {{PROJECT}}-web-admin

Next.js admin console for {{PROJECT}}. Use this console for everything the mobile
app intentionally leaves out: setup, member invitations, owner CRUD, and the
audit log viewer.

## Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router) + React 19
- TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS
- TanStack Query for server state
- React Hook Form + Zod for forms
- NextAuth (Auth.js v5) — Google sign-in exchanged with `user-service`; the
  resulting bearer is forwarded to backend calls. JWT validation lives in
  `user-service` / `{{PROJECT}}-core`, **never** in this app.

## Quick start

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local
npm run dev
```

The dev server listens on `http://localhost:3000` by default. When running
through `docker-compose.dev.yml` it is published on `http://localhost:3001` to
avoid colliding with the backend on `:3000`.

## Scripts

| Command            | What it does                          |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------- |
| `npm run dev`      | Start the Next.js dev server          |
| `npm run build`    | Production build (standalone output)  |
| `npm run start`    | Run the production server             |
| `npm run lint`     | ESLint via `next lint`                |
| `npm run typecheck`| `tsc --noEmit`                        |
| `npm test`         | Vitest (jsdom) one-shot               |
| `npm run test:watch` | Vitest watch mode                   |
